This is unsettling:<p><pre><code>  class Score extends React.Component {
    render() {
      var {initials, score} = this.props.score;
      return (
        <li key={initials}>
          <strong>{initials}</strong> {score}
        </li>
      );
    }
  }
  Score = Relay.createContainer(Score, {
    fragments: {
      score: () => Relay.QL`
        fragment on Score {
          initials,
          score,
        }
      `,
    },
  });
</code></pre>
Soo, if I understood well, first they create a class and then they create a global variable reusing the same name of the class, in order to create and object that expands the class?<p>This Facebook people know how to make me uncomfortable. But I guess I could get used, the same way I got used to JSX...
